Topic: GTO (Group Discussion + GPE) 🔥

👉 Now you’ve entered Stage 2 (after screening)
👉 Here, officers check your leadership in a group

1️⃣ What is GTO?

GTO = Group Testing Officer Tasks
👉 Conducted over Day 3 & Day 4

Today we focus on:

🗣️ Group Discussion (GD)
🗺️ Group Planning Exercise (GPE)
2️⃣ GROUP DISCUSSION (GD)

👉 You’ll be given 2 topics

Topic 1: Current affairs
Topic 2: Social issue

⏱️ Time: ~15–20 minutes

🗣️ How GD Looks
✅ How to Perform in GD
🔹 Start Smart (if possible)
Don’t rush
Speak clearly

👉 Example:
“Good morning everyone, the topic given is… I would like to share my views…”

🔹 During Discussion

✅ Speak 2–3 times
✅ Add points logically
✅ Support others
✅ Listen actively

❌ Avoid
Shouting
Interrupting aggressively
Staying silent
🧠 GD SECRET

👉 You are not competing
👉 You are building discussion

💥 Officer = Team builder

3️⃣ GROUP PLANNING EXERCISE (GPE)

👉 This is MOST IMPORTANT GTO TASK

🗺️ What Happens?

You get:

A map with problems
Multiple situations (accident, robbery, etc.)
🗺️ Example GPE Situation

👉 You must:
1️⃣ Read problem
2️⃣ Write individual plan
3️⃣ Discuss in group
4️⃣ Make common plan

4️⃣ How to Solve GPE (STEP-BY-STEP)
🔹 Step 1: Identify Problems
List all problems clearly
🔹 Step 2: Prioritize

👉 Which is most urgent?

Example:

Life danger → first
Property → later
🔹 Step 3: Resources
People
Time
Distance
Vehicles
🔹 Step 4: Make Practical Plan

👉 Example:
“He divides group, sends injured to hospital, informs police, and reaches next task on time.”

🧠 GOLDEN RULE

👉 Plan must be:

Practical
Time-based
Resource-based
5️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ Unrealistic plans
❌ Ignoring time/distance
❌ Talking without structure
❌ Not participating

6️⃣ PRO STRATEGY (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Show these OLQs:

Leadership
Cooperation
Planning ability
Decision making

💥 Don’t try to dominate
💥 Try to guide group

